PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781923667
OL,3,CHow 'heat dome' is set to break 1976
OL,4,Csummer record with temperatures of 35C
OL,6,FTemperatures will continue to rocket
OL,7,Fthrough France to similar levels, and
OL,8,Fthere's a high chance the heat and
OL,9,Fhumid air will break records.
OL,11,FThis latest heatwave across Europe is
OL,12,Fincreasingly being called a 'heat
OL,13,Fdome', a term that comes from the US.
OL,15,FWhat is a 'heat dome'?
OL,17,FA 'heat dome' is an area of relentless
OL,18,For stubborn high pressure which
OL,19,Fremains stuck over a large area - such
OL,20,Fas the continent - for an increased
OL,21,Flength of time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
