PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781923667
OL,3,CHow 'heat dome' is set to break 1976
OL,4,Csummer record with temperatures of 35C
OL,6,FHot air is trapped underneath it, a
OL,7,Flittle like an atmospheric lid.
OL,9,FThis trapped or stagnant air continues
OL,10,Fto heat up and this, combined with day
OL,11,Fon day strong sunshine, leads to
OL,12,Fprolonged and dangerous heatwaves.
OL,14,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,19,FIt can have profound knock-on effect
OL,20,Fwhen it comes to health warnings and
OL,21,Fimpacts on vegetation and crops.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
