PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781923667
OL,3,CHow 'heat dome' is set to break 1976
OL,4,Csummer record with temperatures of 35C
OL,6,FExpect highs of 30 to 35C across parts
OL,7,Fof the south-east with increasingly
OL,8,Fhumid conditions and some very warm
OL,9,Frestless nights.
OL,11,FAfter a hot start in the south and
OL,12,Fsouth-east, the heat will become more
OL,13,Fof a theme for all of us. Temperatures
OL,14,Fwill climb in northern and western
OL,15,Fareas by Tuesday onwards.
OL,17,FMost of England and Wales will see
OL,18,Fhighs of 30C or close to, and parts of
OL,19,Feastern Scotland will see highs of 27
OL,20,Fto 28C by the middle of the week.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
